==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Primage
<hw>Pri"mage</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>A charge in addition to the freight; originally,
a gratuity to the captain for his particular care of the goods
(sometimes called <altname>hat money</altname>), but now belonging to
the owners or freighters of the vessel, unless by special agreement the
whole or part is assigned to the captain.</def>
<rj><au>Homans.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primal</ent>⟦br⟧
